<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="pleasure-n">pleasure <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pleʒə(r)/    美 /'pleʒər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u-enjoyment">1.★ <strong>[U] 快乐 (enjoyment)；娱乐：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>From her teenage years, she <strong>took pleasure in</strong> writing short stories. 
从十几岁起，她就喜欢写些小故事。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] 乐事；乐趣：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Giving is always a pleasure.
给予永远都是件乐事。</p><footer>2008 北京</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It is <strong>a</strong> great <strong>pleasure to</strong> meet you students from England.
非常高兴认识你们这些从英国来的学生。</p><footer>人教⑧–5</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He enjoyed all the pleasures there were in life. 
他享受生活中所有的乐趣。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="for-pleasure">for pleasure</h3>
<p>1.<strong>作为消遣：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We read mainly for information, not for pleasure. 
我们读书主要是为了获取信息，并非为了消遣。</p></div>

<h3 id="its-a-pleasure-its-my-pleasure">it’s a pleasure / (it’s) my pleasure</h3>
<p>1.<strong>[用于对别人感谢的回答] 别客气；没什么：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Thank you for coming to help us. 
谢谢你来帮助我们。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— It’s a pleasure. / My pleasure.
别客气。</p></div>

<h3 id="with-pleasure">with pleasure</h3>
<p>1.<strong>高兴地；[用于应答] 非常乐意：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Invited into a friend’s home, you should accept with pleasure.
如果被邀请去朋友家做客，你应该高兴地接受。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Would you like to come and have lunch on Sunday? 
你愿意周日来吃午餐吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— With pleasure. I’d love to come. 
当然了，我很乐意来。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>— Could you be so kind as to close the window?
— <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (当然可以). (pleasure)  （2009 安徽改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. With pleasure  </p></div>